# Contributing — Dashboard

## Purpose

Enforce consistent style, passing checks, and clean PRs on the mosbot-dashboard React/Vite app.

## Do

- Use **double quotes** for all JS/JSX string literals and import paths.
- Use **functional components with hooks only** — no class components.
- Place new pages under `src/pages/`, reusable UI under `src/components/`, stores under `src/stores/`.
- Use `classNames()` from `src/utils/helpers.js` for dynamic class composition.
- Use shared constants from `src/utils/constants.js` for statuses, priorities, and columns.
- Reuse shared CSS classes (`btn-primary`, `btn-secondary`, `input-field`, `card`) before adding new ones.
- Name branches: `feat/<short-description>`, `fix/<short-description>`, `chore/<short-description>`.
- Keep PRs focused — one logical change per PR.

## Don't

- Don't create new Axios instances — use the shared `api` from `src/api/client.js`.
- Don't add inline styles when a Tailwind utility or shared class exists.
- Don't commit `node_modules/`, `dist/`, or any build artifact.
- Don't merge a PR with failing lint, test, or build checks.
- Don't introduce new fonts or break the dark-theme color palette.

## Commands

```bash
make lint        # ESLint
make test-run    # Vitest (CI mode)
make build       # Vite production build

# Without Make:
npm run lint
npm run test:run
npm run build
```

## PR Checklist

- [ ] `make lint` passes with no new errors
- [ ] `make test-run` passes
- [ ] `make build` succeeds
- [ ] New UI shows loading **and** error states
- [ ] No hardcoded strings that belong in `constants.js`
- [ ] No secrets, tokens, or internal URLs in code or comments
